annotationA: Uncharacterized protein, isoform C; 5'-nucleotidase activity; nucleoside-triphosphatase activity; nucleoside-diphosphatase activity; metal ion binding; nucleotide binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: nucleotide catabolic process; Belongs to the 5'-nucleotidase family
annotationB: Adenylosuccinate synthetase; Plays an important role in the de novo pathway and in the salvage pathway of purine nucleotide biosynthesis. Catalyzes the first committed step in the biosynthesis of AMP from IMP (By similarity). Plays a role in the regulation of adult life span
